"{\"uid\": \"newsweek.com-paris-olympics-dengue-fever-cases-outbreak-super-spreader-1930096\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Published Jul 25, 2024 at 08:05 AM EDT News Reporter Dengue feveris on the rise, with almost 10 million infections reported in the Americas in the first six months of 2024, according to the World Health Organization (WHO)-twice as many cases as there were in the whole of 2023.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 280, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 193, \"end\": 224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Health_Organization\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Health Organization (WHO)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Health_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Health_Organization\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Published Jul\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 13}, {\"ngram\": \"08:05 AM EDT News Reporter Dengue feveris\", \"from\": 26, \"to\": 67}, {\"ngram\": \"the rise\", \"from\": 71, \"to\": 79}, {\"ngram\": \"almost 10 million infections\", \"from\": 86, \"to\": 114}, {\"ngram\": \"the Americas\", \"from\": 127, \"to\": 139}, {\"ngram\": \"the first six months\", \"from\": 143, \"to\": 163}, {\"ngram\": \"as many cases\", \"from\": 228, \"to\": 241}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole\", \"from\": 259, \"to\": 268}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As Paris prepares to host theOlympics, there is mounting concern that it could become a super spreader event.\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 285, \"end\": 290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999940883, \"rank\": 5.7149139881521614e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theOlympics\", \"from\": 308, \"to\": 319}, {\"ngram\": \"mounting concern\", \"from\": 330, \"to\": 346}, {\"ngram\": \"a super spreader event\", \"from\": 368, \"to\": 390}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Global travel, hot and wet weather, and climate change have created good conditions for the Asian tiger mosquitoes that transmit the disease to thrive.\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 484, \"end\": 506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Asian tiger mosquitoes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Global travel\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 405}, {\"ngram\": \"hot and wet weather\", \"from\": 407, \"to\": 426}, {\"ngram\": \"climate change\", \"from\": 432, \"to\": 446}, {\"ngram\": \"good conditions\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 475}, {\"ngram\": \"the disease\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 532}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Newsweekreached out to the office of the French president via an online form for comment.\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 586, \"end\": 602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French president\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the office\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 578}, {\"ngram\": \"an online form\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 621}, {\"ngram\": \"comment\", \"from\": 626, \"to\": 633}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Denguefever is a mosquito-borne viral infection that has rapidly spread in recent years to become a global health concern.\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 758, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Denguefever\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 647}, {\"ngram\": \"a mosquito-borne viral infection\", \"from\": 651, \"to\": 683}, {\"ngram\": \"recent years\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 723}, {\"ngram\": \"a global health concern\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 757}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is caused by the dengue virus, which is transmitted to humans through the bites of infected Aedes mosquitoes, primarily the Aedes aegypti species.\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 908, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the dengue virus\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 791}, {\"ngram\": \"humans\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 823}, {\"ngram\": \"the bites\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 841}, {\"ngram\": \"infected Aedes mosquitoes\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 870}, {\"ngram\": \"primarily the Aedes\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 891}, {\"ngram\": \"species\", \"from\": 900, \"to\": 907}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The disease is prevalent in tropical and subtropical regions around the world, including Southeast Asia, the Pacific Islands, the Caribbean, South America and parts of Africa, according to WHO.\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 1103, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The disease\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 921}, {\"ngram\": \"tropical and subtropical regions\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 970}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 978, \"to\": 987}, {\"ngram\": \"Southeast Asia\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1013}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pacific Islands\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1034}, {\"ngram\": \"the Caribbean\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1049}, {\"ngram\": \"South America\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1064}, {\"ngram\": \"parts\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1074}, {\"ngram\": \"Africa\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1084}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A WHO spokesperson explained toNewsweekthat: \\\"Dengueis a mosquito-borne virus not endemic in the WHO European Region and reported cases are mainly travel-related.\", \"from\": 1105, \"to\": 1267, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A WHO spokesperson\", \"from\": 1105, \"to\": 1123}, {\"ngram\": \"Dengueis\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1159}, {\"ngram\": \"a mosquito-borne virus\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1182}, {\"ngram\": \"the WHO European Region\", \"from\": 1198, \"to\": 1221}, {\"ngram\": \"reported cases\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, as the mosquitoes that transmit dengue (tiger mosquitoes) are widely present in Europe there have been sporadic autochthonous dengue cases and a few dengue outbreaks reported in the region since 2010 with evidence of dengue transmission from five countries, including France.\\\"\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1553, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1545, \"end\": 1551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999925138361595, \"rank\": 3.138580270811242e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the mosquitoes\", \"from\": 1280, \"to\": 1294}, {\"ngram\": \"dengue\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1315}, {\"ngram\": \"tiger mosquitoes\", \"from\": 1317, \"to\": 1333}, {\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1363}, {\"ngram\": \"sporadic autochthonous dengue cases\", \"from\": 1380, \"to\": 1415}, {\"ngram\": \"a few dengue outbreaks\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1442}, {\"ngram\": \"the region\", \"from\": 1455, \"to\": 1465}, {\"ngram\": \"evidence\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1490}, {\"ngram\": \"dengue transmission\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1513}, {\"ngram\": \"five countries\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1533}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Preventative Measures Newsweekspoke with a Paris 2024 spokesperson, who said: \\\"Paris 2024 is working closely with the health authorities to identify and deploy appropriate prevention and monitoring measures.\\\"\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1764, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1599, \"end\": 1609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.172169792311905e-13, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Preventative Measures Newsweekspoke\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1590}, {\"ngram\": \"Paris\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1639}, {\"ngram\": \"the health authorities\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1691}, {\"ngram\": \"appropriate prevention and monitoring measures\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1761}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They confirmed that \\\"45 ecological mosquito traps will be installed at the Olympic and Paralympic Village and 15 at the Marseille Marina.\\\"\", \"from\": 1766, \"to\": 1904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1853, \"end\": 1871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paralympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"45 ecological mosquito traps\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1815}, {\"ngram\": \"the Marseille Marina\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1902}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The WHO representative explained that \\\"WHO has a dedicated team of experts working on mass gatherings, including sport events.\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 2032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1906, \"end\": 1913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Who\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The WHO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Who\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Who\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a dedicated team\", \"from\": 1953, \"to\": 1969}, {\"ngram\": \"experts\", \"from\": 1973, \"to\": 1980}, {\"ngram\": \"mass gatherings\", \"from\": 1992, \"to\": 2007}, {\"ngram\": \"sport events\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2031}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The role in the mass gatherings team is to provide guidance, tools and expertise to the organizer, host governments for health planning and safe delivery of mass gathering events using a risk-based approach.\\\"\", \"from\": 2033, \"to\": 2241, \"entities\": [], \"no